xtraordinary legal measures that targeted Jews alone. This book examines the origins and implementation of the numerus clausus, as well as the attempts to dampen its impact on Hungary's international reputation, focusing on the debates surrounding it promulgation (1920), its modification (1928) and its eventual application to other areas of Jewish life (1938-45).  afunded by Opening the Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAntisemitismzHungaryxHistoryy20th century. 0aCivil servicezHungaryxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewsxEducationzHungaryxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewsxLegal status, laws, etc.zHungaryxHistoryy20th c entury. 0aNumerus claususzHungaryxHistoryy20th century. 0aRace defilement (Nuremberg Laws of 1935). 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aAnti-Jewish Laws.  aAntisemitism.  aInterwar Hungary.  aJewish Question.1 aMiller, Michael L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aOpening the Futureefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2023z978311079759608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789633866214?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633866214zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.de